    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" id="faq">
    <h2>FAQ</h2>

    <h3>What is £26,000 after tax per month?</h3>
    <p class="muted">
      A £26,000 salary in the UK is approximately <b>£1,787 per month</b> after tax and National Insurance, based on a simple 2025/26 estimate.
    </p>

    <h3>What is £26,000 after tax per week?</h3>
    <p class="muted">
      The weekly take-home pay for a £26,000 salary is roughly <b>£412 per week</b>.
    </p>

    <h3>Does this include pension or student loan deductions?</h3>
    <p class="muted">
      No. This page uses a simple estimate and does not include pension contributions, student loans, or other personal deductions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="muted">
      <b>Disclaimer:</b> This page provides a simplified salary estimate for general guidance only. Actual take-home pay may differ depending on your tax code, pension, student loan plan, benefits, bonuses, and other deductions.
    </div>
  </div>

